    "Henri Stern specialized in the study of iconography of mosaics from Late Antiquity through the Middle Ages, Syrian art of the 5th and 6th centuries, and early Islamic art more broadly.": [],
    "Yet, he was intentional in his approach to studying mosaics in relation to several other art techniques, mainly wall paintings, ivories, and sarcophagi (Barral I Altet).": [
